Based on the assumption in your comments, you can look for lags to define where the groups start based on the relative prices.  Then do a cumulative sum of the &quot;group starts&quot; to calculate a grouping id, and aggregate:

    select item, min(price), max(price), count(*)
    from (select i.*,
                 count(*) over (filter where prev_price &lt; 0.9 * price) over (partition by item order by price) as grp
          from (select i.*,
                       lag(price) over (partition by item order by price) as prev_price
                from items i
               ) i
         ) i
    group by item
    order by item, min(price);

