answers.body_markdown:
In a subquery, you could use [regexp functions `regexp_replace()` and `regexp_extract()`](https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/Hive/LanguageManual+UDF) to separate the value from the suffix. Then, you can aggregate and apply the logic in the outer query:

	select 
		value,
		case 
			when min(suffix) = &#39;_NEWFORMAT&#39; and max(suffix) = &#39;_OLDDAT&#39; 
				then &#39;Contains both NEW and OLD&#39;
			when max(suffix) = &#39;_NEWFORMAT&#39;
				then &#39;Missing OLD&#39;
			else &#39;Missing NEW&#39;
		end reason
	from (
		select 
			regexp_replace(datalist, &#39;_OLDDAT|_NEWFORMAT$&#39;, &#39;&#39;) value,
			regexp_extract(datalist, &#39;(_OLDDAT|_NEWFORMAT)$&#39;, 1) suffix
		from mytable
	) x
	group by value

